[*][b]Nakizakura Kitan[/b]: While wandering about, Masachika stops by to watch a traveling troupe perform. Captivated by the sight of an oni maiden dancing in a whirl of cherry blossoms, he redeems her and takes her as his traveling companion. He names her Ouka and treats her kindly. She slowly opens up to him; however, having experienced little warmth in her life, she is also unsettled by his kindness. As for her final resolve&hellip;
[*][b]Mugen Dokei[/b]: In a world where time consists of two kinds of clocks, the Clock of Eternity, which indicates the life span of the universe, and the Silver Clock, which indicates the life span of a person, lived Mu, a carefree girl who despises the contradiction between eternity and the Clocks. Then she meets a boy who&rsquo;s Silver Clock runs faster than any other person she&rsquo;s met&hellip;
[*][b]Sandglass no Ori[/b]: A boy with no memories was taken in by an elderly couple. With no identity and recurring dreams, he lived his life, as what it is.
[*][b]Hana no Canon[/b]: Flowers, accompanying us from the beginning to the ending.
